{#-
  Sonner — toast viewport markup (Ring 2 S2.5).

  This template renders the viewport `<aside>` that the SonnerController
  manages at runtime. In normal Stimulus boot (`boot()` from
  `@gerard/theme`), the `ensureSonnerViewport()` helper auto-injects this
  markup into `document.body` once — consumers do not need to include
  this template manually.

  Use this include ONLY if:
    - Consumer prefers SSR-rendered viewport (e.g. for layout stability
      on long FCP — empty viewport injected by JS would flash).
    - Consumer is in `register()` (manual) mode without calling `boot()`,
      and prefers Twig over a manual `ensureSonnerViewport()` JS call.

  Usage:
    {% include '@theme/components/sonner/sonner.html.twig' %}

  Place near the closing `</body>` tag so the viewport sits at the end of
  the DOM (top-layer with `position: fixed` + `z-index: var(--z-toast)`
  doesn't strictly need this, but body-end placement keeps the
  source-order intuitive for SR users navigating with virtual cursor —
  notifications land at the document tail like footnotes).

  The viewport is **content-empty** — toasts are rendered inside it by
  the SonnerController at runtime (`window.themeToast.show({...})` or
  `document.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('theme:toast:show', {...}))`).

  Per [12-microcopy-tone.md §Toasts] the variant/duration defaults are
  baked into the controller (success 4s, success+undo 10s, info ∞,
  warning 6s, danger ∞). Consumers override per-call via the JS API.

  Microcopy keys used by the controller:
    - theme.sonner.aria.viewport    — landmark aria-label
    - theme.sonner.aria.dismiss     — dismiss-x aria-label (per toast)
    - theme.sonner.queue-more.{one,other} — "+N autres" plural indicator
    - theme.sonner.default-label.{success,info,warning,danger} — fallback
      when consumer omits `message`
    - theme.sonner.default-undo-label — fallback when consumer's
      `undoLabel` is absent

  Doctrine (per Sonner spec §3, §7):
    - role: native <aside> with aria-label (landmark per 13-a11y §13).
    - Per-toast role auto-derives from variant — set by the controller
      (success/info/warning → <output> with implicit role="status" +
      aria-live="polite" ; danger → <div role="alert"> assertive).
    - Pointer events: viewport is `pointer-events: none` so the empty
      gap region between toasts passes clicks through to page content
      below ; each rendered toast re-enables pointer events.
-#}
<aside class="theme-sonner__viewport"
       aria-label="{{ 'theme.sonner.aria.viewport'|trans }}"
       data-controller="sonner"
       data-action="pointerenter->sonner#pauseAll pointerleave->sonner#resumeAll keydown.esc@window->sonner#dismissAll">
  {# Queue indicator — initially hidden. SonnerController toggles
     `hidden` + textContent ("+N autres") as the queue grows. #}
  <button type="button"
          class="theme-sonner__queue-indicator"
          data-action="click->sonner#expandQueue"
          data-sonner-target="indicator"
          hidden></button>
</aside>
